Revaxis is a Diphtheria, Tetanus and Poliomyelitis (inactivated) vaccine manufactured by Sanofi Pasteur. This vaccine helps boost protection against diphtheria, tetanus and poliomyelitis (polio).

Revaxis is used for preventing diphtheria, tetanus and polio in children from six years of age, adolescents and adults. Revaxis is used for a booster vaccination against these diseases. It is given to teenagers at 14 years of age as part of the British childhood immunisation schedule.

LYMErix [Lyme Disease Vaccine (Recombinant OspA)] is a noninfectious recombinant vaccine developed and manufactured by SmithKline Beecham Biologicals. The vaccine contains lipoprotein OspA, an outer surface protein of Borrelia burgdorferi sensu stricto ZS7, as expressed by Escherichia coli. Lipoprotein OspA is a single polypeptide chain of 257 amino acids with lipids covalently bonded to the N terminus.
